I&#39;ve recently revisited ArgoUML (v0.12) and found it to work quite well for
creating quick and dirty class diagrams.

Import your source files; delete the classes that you&#39;re not interested in
seeing; then hit print. Grab the tape dispenser and head for the printer..
:)

I usually end up w/ 3x3 page printouts that I can then color on.

The &quot;Type-Hierarchy&quot; view in Eclipse (&WSAD) can also be very useful to get
a quick idea of what relationships exist.

